# Push to Deploy

When the user says **"Push"** (or "push" or "deploy"), run these commands in the terminal so the user can see the output:

1. `git status` — show what will be committed
2. `git add .`
3. `git commit -m "..."` — use a brief descriptive message (e.g., "Update river list padding") or ask the user for one
4. `git push`

Run each command separately (or as a single chained command) so the terminal displays the output. Netlify is connected to the repo, so pushing automatically triggers a build and deploy.
